summary:
I have 20+ years experience in accounting.
Before the war I was chief accountant & finance manager in a construction engineering company in Ukraine.  
I am currently living in the Netherlands, I completed an accounting course on European law and I have sertificat.
For me, being an accountant is more than just performing job duties. It's an engaging and creative process that involves thinking beyond the standard list of responsibilities. I specialize in finding innovative solutions, developing financial strategies, and analyzing data to benefit the company. With experience in various industries, I am dedicated to continuous improvement and staying up-to-date with the latest trends and best practices.
I understand that I will need to learn a lot of new things in my new country, and I would like to find a full-time assistant position to learn the whole process from the very beginning. I would be grateful for your suggestions.
